'''Puthuponnani''' ([[Malayalam]]:<U+0D2A><U+0D41><U+0D24><U+0D41><U+0D2A><U+0D4A><U+0D28><U+0D4D><U+0D28><U+0D3E><U+0D28><U+0D3F>) is costal locality in [[Ponnani taluk]] of [[Malappuram district]] in the state of [[Kerala]], [[India]].

==Description==
[[File:Puthuponnani (2).JPG|thumb|250px|left|a scene from puthuponnani promontory]]
Puthuponnani borderes  [[Arabian sea]] to the west and  [[Canoli Canal]] to the east. Puthuponnani is coming under Ponnani [[municipality]]. 

Puthuponnani<U+2019>s promontory where Canoli Canal falls [[Arabian Sea]] is place for people coming to  relax and enjoy sunset in evening time. [[Veliyankode]] is nearby place.

==Society==

As a place of socially and economically backward when compared with other parts of taluk, most of the peoplels<U+2019> livelihood is fishing and daily wage works. Some of them migrated to [[Arab states of the Persian Gulf|Gulf]] countries to find their bread and butter.Few people working at Educational (Govt.and Private) and conventional agricultural sectors.

